primaryTopic.definition: The centre's research focuses on enhancing the environmental, economic, social and cultural well-being of south-western Australia and elsewhere. The Centre is located in Western Australia's Great Southern region, a global hotspot of biodiversity. The centre complements its research through applied consultancy, education and communication.
